title: Merge pull request #1 from ideco/master
message:
Merge pull request #1 from ideco/master

Fixed performance bug and re-factored FullDijkstra

title: Refactored FullDijkstra and introduced UnreachableNodeProvider
message:
Refactored FullDijkstra and introduced UnreachableNodeProvider

Up to now, FullDijkstra was a standalone implementation of Dijkstra's algorithm which had nothing in common with the other implementations in this project, which all inherit from AbstractDijkstra.

Since this class was only used to compute the unreachable nodes in the graph, it was removed and replaced by UnreachableNodeProvider, which contains a nested implementation of Dijkstra's algorithm, which inherits from PriorityDijkstra.

title: Fixed bug that reduced routing performance
message:
Fixed bug that reduced routing performance

When scanning new arcs in Dijkstra's algorithm, it makes sense to check whether the target of the new ark has already been visited and to not scan such arks again.
Up to now however, we always checked if the target of the whole route has already been visited, which hardly makes any sense at all.
Although this typo did not have any impact on the behaviour of the algorithm (the computed routes were still correct) it did have impact on the performance. It was now fixed, and as a consequence the routing algorithms should run faster.
